OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1775473374
OL,3,CScientists identify trigger of Crohn's
OL,4,Cscarring, research suggests
OL,6,FResearch suggests scientists have
OL,7,Fidentified what drives the development
OL,8,Fof scar tissue in the intestines of
OL,9,Fpeople with Crohn's disease.
OL,11,FScientists found clusters of immune
OL,12,Fcells in the gut which may be
OL,13,Fstimulating nearby cells to generate
OL,14,Fexcess scar tissue, known as fibrosis.
OL,16,FIt is hoped the discovery, detailed in
OL,17,Fa new study, could help develop
OL,18,Ftreatments to prevent or slow the
OL,19,Fdevelopment of fibrosis, a serious
OL,20,Fcomplication of Crohn's disease.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/10
