PN,30904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1775473374
OL,3,CScientists identify trigger of Crohn's
OL,4,Cscarring, research suggests
OL,6,FDr Shahida Din, consultant
OL,7,Fgastroenterologist at NHS Lothian and
OL,8,Fhonorary senior clinical lecturer at
OL,9,Fthe University of Edinburgh, said:
OL,10,F"Fibrosis remains one of the most
OL,11,Fchallenging complications of Crohn's
OL,12,Fdisease because current treatments
OL,13,Fprimarily target inflammation rather
OL,14,Fthan the scarring itself.
OL,16,F"Understanding the cellular signalling
OL,17,Fpathways that link immune activity to
OL,18,Fcollagen production could help guide
OL,19,Fthe development of therapies aimed at
OL,20,Fpreventing or slowing fibrosis."
OL,26,@rD@AOUxD@AOU|D@`O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
