PN,30905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1775473374
OL,3,CScientists identify trigger of Crohn's
OL,4,Cscarring, research suggests
OL,6,FThe research team analysed intestinal
OL,7,Ftissue samples from Crohn's disease
OL,8,Fpatients with fibrosis, focusing on
OL,9,Fthe ileum ` the final part of the
OL,10,Fsmall intestine where the disease most
OL,11,Fcommonly develops.
OL,13,FThe researchers used archived
OL,14,Fintestinal tissue samples to examine
OL,15,Fstructural changes across the
OL,16,Fdifferent layers of the bowel wall.
OL,18,FThey found significantly increased
OL,19,Ffibrosis and immune cell infiltration
OL,20,Fin Crohn's disease tissue compared
OL,21,Fwith normal tissue.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
