PN,30907
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1775473374
OL,3,CScientists identify trigger of Crohn's
OL,4,Cscarring, research suggests
OL,6,FThey identified a link between
OL,7,Fclusters of immune cells, known as
OL,8,FCrohn's lymphoid aggregates, and
OL,9,Fgroups of endothelial cells, which
OL,10,Fnormally line blood vessels.
OL,12,FScientists found that the endothelial
OL,13,Fcells appeared to form distinctive
OL,14,Fstructures surrounding the Crohn's
OL,15,Flymphoid aggregates.
OL,17,FFurther analysis revealed signalling
OL,18,Finteractions between these clusters
OL,19,Fand nearby cells responsible for
OL,20,Fproducing collagen, suggesting they
OL,21,Fmay actively promote fibrosis.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
