PN,30908
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1775473374
OL,3,CScientists identify trigger of Crohn's
OL,4,Cscarring, research suggests
OL,6,FDr Michael Glinka, research fellow at
OL,7,Fthe University of Edinburgh, said:
OL,8,F"Our findings highlight previously
OL,9,Funrecognised interactions between
OL,10,Fimmune cells, endothelial cells and
OL,11,Fcollagen-producing cells in Crohn's
OL,12,Fdisease.
OL,14,F"By combining traditional pathology
OL,15,Fwith single-cell transcriptomics, we
OL,16,Fwere able to confirm these changes
OL,17,Fusing two independent approaches and
OL,18,Funcover biological signalling pathways
OL,19,Fthat may provide new therapeutic
OL,20,Ftargets."
OL,26,@pD@AOUvD@AOU|D@IO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/10
